  "body": "## Preamble\r\n\r\n    VIP: 837\r\n    Title: Custom units in convert\r\n    Author: Ben Kaufman\r\n    Type: Standard Track\r\n    Status: Draft\r\n    Created: 2018-05-24\r\n\r\n\r\n## Simple Summary\r\nAllow specifying custom units when using convert.\r\n\r\n## Abstract\r\nAllow specifying custom units when using convert.\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\nCurrently, we can only use ``convert`` for a base value, I think we should also be able to use it in order to set a unit.\r\n\r\n## Specification\r\nI think it should look like this:\r\n``convert(value, 'uint256(some_unit)')``\r\n\r\n## Backwards Compatibility\r\nThis should be backwards compatible\r\n\r\n## Copyright\r\nCopyright and related rights waived via [CC0](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/)\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Cute Animal Picture\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10667901/40490438-2e63bf32-5f74-11e8-81e6-9aaa02ed576d.png)\r\n\r\n",
