    "body": "I think that `convert` should not let you drop units. You should have to use the explicit `as_unitless_number` call for that.\r\n\r\nI would expect the following the throw because it is implicitly dropping the unit. \r\n```python\r\nvalue: int128(unit) = 50.0\r\nnew_value: uint256 = convert(value, 'uint256')\r\n```\r\n\r\nand I would expect the following to succeed\r\n```python\r\nvalue: int128(unit) = 50.0\r\nnew_value: uint256(unit) = convert(value, 'uint256(unit)')\r\n```\r\n\r\nI also don't think you should be able to add units via convert.",
