    "body": "I'm not sure about dropping units because most time I would expect units to have a certain type so if I convert a variable with unit it should drop the unit, but maybe we do need to change it for the sake of explicitly.\r\n\r\nWhy don't you think we should add custom units in convert? There are certain cases where adding a unit in other way would be very difficult and inefficient. For example:\r\n```\r\nunits: {\r\n    cm: \"centimeter\"\r\n}\r\n\r\n@public\r\ndef foo():\r\n    num1: uint256(cm) = convert(10, 'uint256')\r\n```\r\nThis won't compile... ",
