    "body": "That last suggestion is interesting (for example, with `ether` to `wei` unit conversions), but it requires associations to built into the units to work correctly.\r\n\r\nSomething like:\r\n```python\r\nunits: {\r\n    cm: \"centimeter\",\r\n    m: \"meter\"\r\n}\r\nconversions: {\r\n    m: 100*cm\r\n}\r\n\r\n@public\r\ndef foo(num1: uint256(cm)):\r\n    num2: uint256(m) = num1/ 100\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis may lead into an entire sub-language of units.",
